## Description
The **Distribute Hybrids (SA) **task allows to define distribution rules for hybrid mail channels, enriching digital documents according to printing and distribution providers.

> Tip

It is also possible to enable the aggregation of shipments and define an aggregation query, without having to add the [**Aggregate Shipments (SA)**](/doxee-platform/docs/aggregate-shipments-sa-batch-workflow-task-reference)** **task to the workflow.

## Configuration
**![](data:image/png;base64,)**

- In the **Alias **field, enter the name of the task that will be displayed in the workflow.

- In the **Site **field, select the instance from which to retrieve the Staging &amp; Aggregation configurations.

> Note

Each tenant is associated with a site. A site may be associated with one or more tenants.

The endpoint used to access the S&amp;A service is: *&lt;site endpoint&gt;/&lt;portal path&gt;/sa/&lt;operation path&gt;*.

- In the **Input &gt; Reference file **section, click **Configure **to display the configuration fields.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

In the **File **field, upload a sample Staging &amp; Aggregation input resource, so that the system understands the XML format that is being used.

- In the **Shipment element **field, specify the element that identifies the shipment (for example: */FILE/SHIPMENT*).

- In the **Document element **field, specify the element that identifies the document (for example: */FILE/SHIPMENT/DOCUMENT*).

- Click **Save **to confirm.

> Tip

Once this section is configured, the panel displays the selected shipment and document elements and the available attributes. You may also click  ![](data:image/png;base64,)  to download the XML reference file; for example:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- In the **Aggregation **section, select the **Enable aggregation **option to define distribution rules to aggregate shipments and documents in the flows.![](data:image/png;base64,)

In the **Aggregation query **field, you may enter the following queries:

**GROUP BY **[*criteria*]

- **ORDER BY **[*criteria*] **ASC **| **DESC**

> Important

The query must contain at least one statement.

The system will use the configured attributes to provide contextual suggestions when building queries.

> Note

The query syntax is:

`GROUP BY argument [, argument] *
ORDER BY argument ASC|DESC [, argument ASC|DESC] `For example:

`GROUP BY foo
ORDER BY bar ASC`- In the **Distribution **section:

From the **Distribution profile **drop-down menu, select the required configuration profile representing the collection of customizable configuration rules that facilitate the process of defining a task.

- From the **Envelope profile **drop-down menu, select the configuration catalog containing the rules for the definition of the type of envelope to use for sending documents.

- From the **Attachment profile **drop-down menu, select the configuration catalog defining which commercial documents must be included in the envelope.

- *(optional) *In the **Attachment attribute **field, enter the name of the attribute to define the attachment type.

- From the **Sheet profile **drop-down menu, select the configuration catalog containing the rules for the definition of the type of sheet to use for sending documents.

- To define a new **Distribution**, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Add**) and fill in the required fields.

> Important

You must define at least one distribution.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Enter the **Distribution name **of the new distribution rule.

- Select to **Use as default **option to set the current distribution as the default one.

> Important

Only one distribution may be set as default.

- Select the digital **Distribution channel **to assign to the new distribution.

- Select the required **Delivery product **from the list.

- *(optional) *In the **Tracking number system**, enter the registered letter's tracking number.

- *(optional) *Select the required **ZIP catalog **from the list.

> Note

If empty, the system uses the latest version of the ZIP catalog.

- In the **Distribution query **field, you may enter the following queries:

**SELECT ALL**

- **SELECT BY**

- **ORDER BY**

- **SPLIT BY**

- **LIMIT BY**

- **LOOKUP BY**

- **TRACK ALL**

- **TRACK WHEN**

> **Valid from Doxee Platform 3 - Build 3.29**

The previously used **WITH LIMIT **statement has been deprecated, and has been replaced by **LIMIT BY**.

> Important

The query must contain at least one statement.

The query must contain the statement **SELECT ALL **or **SELECT BY**.

> Note

The system will use the configured attributes to provide contextual suggestions when building queries. 

The query syntax is:

`SELECT ALL | SELECT BY selector [AND|OR selector]* LOOKUP BY attribute [, attribute]*
ORDER BY attribute ASC|DESC [, attribute ASC|DESC]* SPLIT BY attribute [, attribute]*
LIMIT BY number [DOCUMENTS|PAGES]`The condition format is:

`attribute =|!=|&lt;|&lt;=|&gt;|&gt;= "value"`For example:

`SELECT ALL
ORDER BY foo ASC 
SPLIT BY bar 
LIMIT BY 10 PAGES`> Important

The input XML and PGG files received by the Distribute Hybrids (SA) task must have the same base name (for example, if the PGG file is called *test.pgg *then the XML file must be called *test.xml*) in order to properly pair the PGG file to the corresponding XML file.

The task will rearrange the shipments (and the contained documents) according to the specified queries, creating a separate output branch for each distribution.

> Note

The system processes distribution rules according to the order in which they appear. If a shipment does not match the first rule, the system processes the next. When a shipment matches a rule, the system ignores all other rules.

The last rule of the table is the failover rule. This rule groups all shipments that the system was not able to associate with the previous rules, regardless of the ZIP catalog of the associated delivery provider. The failover rule must not contain other control conditions.

> Note

This task has output branches for all the configured distributions (using distribution name as branch name) and the predefined "All files" branch, that allows to include all outputs; for example:
